hat a real queue enforces capacity. Real failure: queue capacity limit is not enforced (e.g., queue allows more events than configured). Only an integration test against a real queue with real capacity limits catches this. Must use actual queue (SQLite, Redis, RabbitMQ, etc.) to verify enforcement.","test_description":"Fill a real queue to its configured capacity limit. Attempt to add one more event. Verify the addition is rejected or returns an error indicating the queue is full.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.92,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13515,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13515},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3d323c85-2476-4a8d-8f0c-6350e2c2f447","uuid":"3d92ecea-b729-428d-88e7-eca684c5421a"}
